>
>+200 <wav 2>"actor" <svp start> /  <ms% 500> "1" /  <ms% 250> /  <ms% 50>
>"2" / <wav 2>"actor" <svp start>  / <ms% 450> "2" /   <ms% 250> / <ms%
100> "3"
>
>The first 800ms involves 500ms of "1", 250ms empty frame and the first 50ms
>of the next number, "2", then the sound file cueing the remaining 450ms of
>the number etc.  I could use %N to keep the item on the screen as the next
>sound file played but I am not sure that would gain me much, would it?

